\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Responsive HTML Enewsletter Checklist
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl312\slmult1
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl312\slmult1

\f0\b \cf0 Starting Out
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\ri0\sl312\slmult1

\f0 \cf0 ____ Copy this doc into the folder of the project you're working on and check off each item.
\f1 \

\f0 ____ Review enewsletter design with Lydia to know what areas should be images/editable text.
\f1 \

\f0 ____ Slice out images from Photoshop. Use {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://thesiteslinger.com/blog/how-to-make-slicing-suck-less-tips-and-tricks-for-slicing-a-psd/"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc0 this article}}
\f1  to make slicing easier.\

\f0 ____ Use our standard 
\b enewsletter-template.html
\b0  that includes many fixes in the <head> and <body> tags. \cf3 Do not delete these tags. \cf0 Add your initials and date to the html comment.\uc0\u8232 
\f1 \
\pard\tx0\pardeftab720\sl312\slmult1

\f0\b \cf0 Best Practices
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\ri0\sl312\slmult1

\f0 \cf0 ____ Align all cells left, top, etc.
\f1 \

\f0 ____ Use alt tags for all images with text; use alt=\'94\'94 for spacer gifs and other layout graphics
\f1 \

\f0 ____ Define width and height for ALL images
\f1 \

\f0 ____ Add border=0 or border:none to linked images
\f1 \

\f0 ____ Add padded table to all photos that are incorporated within each article in order to \'93float\'94 images. \cf4 Do not use borders to create this space.
\f1 \cf0 \

\f0 ____ Make as easy as possible for client to edit \'96 create large areas of editable text 
\f1 \

\f0 ____ Every rule in media query must have \cf4 !important\cf0  written after it to fix a bug in Yahoo webmail.
\f1 \

\f0 ____ Add display:block wherever possible to remove unwanted space around images. Always use this on spacer gifs.
\f1 \

\f0 ____ Fix small spacer gifs from being blown up larger in Outlook 2013 (you can anticipate this with any gif less than ~10px high) See Troubleshooting Doc for instructions.\
____ If content background color is different from the overall template background color, add a 620px width table somewhere in the template so that there is a bit of margin showing to the left and right of the content. See PATNC enews template as an example. This fixes the content from butting up against the sides of the email window in: Gmail, Yahoo, AOL.
\f1 \
\pard\tx0\pardeftab720\sl312\slmult1

\f0 \cf0  
\f1 \
