\f0\b \cf0 Testing/Cleaning Up
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\ri0\sl312\slmult1

\f0 \cf0 ____ Check for missing cells. Browsers will self-correct but Dreamweaver can you show you where they are missing.
\f1 \

\f0 ____ In Dreamweaver, select View > Code view options > Highlight invalid code then scan your html for anything you may have missed. (Leave this setting turned on)
\f1 \

\f0 ____ Remove any unused code when finished for example unused styles. Open the newsletter in Chrome, go to Web Developer Tools > Audits and run an Audit on the page. It will show you the unused styles.
\f1 \

\f0 ____ Upload all images to the server and change all image links to absolute. Upload your sliced photoshop file to the server as well.
\f1 \

\f0 ____ \cf3 TEST in your browser \cf0 to make sure responsive aspects work properly. Chrome is a good indicator of what will iPhones will display.
\f1 \

\f0 ____\cf3  TEST in Litmus\cf0  for email client consistency and make adjustments if necessary. Add the client acronym as a Tag on the test, for example \'93aafp\'94 or \'93nccbh\'94
\f1 \

\f0 ____ After testing and going through this checklist, give link to the email and to the Litmus test to Lydia for review.
\f1 \
